--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This file lists changes made to the Ansible role. It follows semantic versioning
guidelines. The content is sorted in reverse chronological order and formatted
to allow easy grepping by scripts.

The fields are:
B: bug
C: change
E: enhancement
F: feature

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Version 5.4.0 (2020-12-31)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.2-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE

* Version 5.3.4 (2020-12-20)
E: Modify 'textfile_collector' path to comply with BSD directory structure

* Version 5.3.3 (2020-12-10)
B: Correct Jinja2 statement in Monit check

* Version 5.3.2 (2020-12-10)
B: Fix Monit check to support asterisk '*' value in openntpd_listen parameter

* Version 5.3.1 (2020-11-29)
B: Adjust return code for monit service check

* Version 5.3.0 (2020-11-28)
F: Add support for Monit service monitoring (openntpd_monitor_monit_state)

* Version 5.2.2 (2020-11-19)
E: Ensure lineinfile tasks can create file if missing

* Version 5.2.1 (2020-10-30)
E: Simplify Ansible file header (ansible_managed)

* Version 5.2.0 (2020-10-19)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.8
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.7

* Version 5.1.3 (2020-08-18)
B: Assign offset_raw variable
E: Minor script improvements

* Version 5.1.2 (2020-08-18)
B: Fix echo commands (BSD echo does not support backslash character sequences)

* Version 5.1.1 (2020-07-07)
B: Add missing openntpd_check_time_state condition

* Version 5.1.0 (2020-07-03)
F: Add support for monitoring via Prometheus node_exporter (textfile_collector)

* Version 5.0.0 (2020-07-03)
C: Redesign cron tasks (use Ansible cron module)
C: Remove option 'openntpd_check_time_interval'
C: Add option 'openntpd_check_time_minute' to specify interval (Default: '*/10')

* Version 4.0.0 (2020-07-02)
C: Move scripts to '/usr/local/sbin'
E: Remove 'common' role dependency

* Version 3.5.0 (2020-05-19)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.7
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.6

* Version 3.4.0 (2019-11-08)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE

* Version 3.3.0 (2019-10-18)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.6
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.5

* Version 3.2.0 (2019-05-26)
F: Port role to Ansible 2.8

* Version 3.1.0 (2019-04-27)
C: Add support for OpenBSD 6.5
C: Drop support for OpenBSD 6.4

* Version 3.0.0 (2019-01-24)
C: Rename option 'openntpd_monitor_mail_recipient' to 'openntpd_monitor_mail_from_address'
C: Rename option 'openntpd_monitor_mail_sender' to 'openntpd_monitor_mail_to_address'

* Version 2.1.2 (2019-01-22)
E: Improve script by throwing error message if script is executed interactively

* Version 2.1.1 (2019-01-21)
E: Improve script and reduce noise by removing echo command from alerting function

* Version 2.1.0 (2019-01-13)
C: Add support for FreeBSD 12.0-RELEASE
C: Drop support for FreeBSD 11.2-RELEASE

* Version 2.0.5 (2019-01-09)
B: Fix issue introduced with improvements to prevent globbing and word splitting

* Version 2.0.4 (2019-01-09)
B: Fix issue introduced with improvements to prevent globbing and word splitting

* Version 2.0.3 (2019-01-09)
E: Improve Shell script to prevent globbing and word splitting

* Version 2.0.2 (2019-01-08)
E: Improve wording in Shell script

* Version 2.0.1 (2019-01-08)
B: Improve return value verification and fix unexpected operator/operand issue
E: Improve Shell script to prevent globbing and word splitting

* Version 2.0.0 (2018-12-23)
C: Mark Ansible role as 'stable'
E: Minor style improvement

* Version 1.1.2 (2018-12-10)
B: Fix 'mailx' command for OpenBSD systems

* Version 1.1.1 (2018-12-10)
B: Add missing Ansible role dependencies

* Version 1.1.0 (2018-12-10)
F: Add option to set system time offset limit (openntpd_check_time_offset_limit)

* Version 1.0.0 (2018-12-09)
F: Redesign 'openntpd_listen' parameter
F: Redesign 'openntpd_server' parameter
C: Add support for 'servers' option (openntpd_servers)
F: Add 'openntpd_check-time' health check

